messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 02/06/2002 9:46:15 PM Eastern Standard Time,
AlwaysLearning@yahoogroups.com writes:


> Happy Birthday Kathryn! I am curious about your 41 presents, please share
> some of the little things you recevied? My bday is next week, I want to
> know
> what to ask for LOL.
>
> From the other Katheryn who usually signs Kathy cos for some reason
> my K teacher thought I should be nicknamed Kathy. I keep thinking one
> day I will reclaim my "real" name....My relatives still call my Katheryn
> though and dh sometimes...
>

Some of the presents: Two really cool books, a little "#1 Mama" trophy, a
flowered lei, a tiger print change purse, a heart straw, a giant pink die, a
heart shped Pez dispenser, little tiny soaps, a little square yoyo, jacks,
play money, a five color pen, a cat nose, etc. All of them came with little
lovey explanations ("When you're down, he yoy will remind you that they'll be
up again.").

I was Kathie (Kathie Jean to relatives, as I had an aunt Cathy) until college
when I started calling myself Kathryn. I am patient with relatives who call
me Kathie.

turning 40 (stupid, yes), and I was surprised with: a video/digital camera, a
HUGE surprise party, AND a trip to London.

I have a VERY good family :)

From: KathrynJB@...

Sent: Wednesday, February 06, 2002 5:25 PM

It's my birthday today (41) and I had a GREAT day planned by my partner and
son. At midnight last night they brought cake in. Then this morning I got 41
presents (mostly little fun things), and then we had an Artist Day, with the
main activity going to a Paint your own ceramics place.

Great fun!
Kathryn
